{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idce03d9cb-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8","identifier":"/us/usc/t47/s765b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"765b"},"text":"§ 765b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Elimination of procurement preferences","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this subchapter or the Communications Act of 1934 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t47/s151"},"text":"47 U.S.C. 151","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall be construed to authorize or require any preference, in Federal Government procurement of telecommunications services, for the satellite space segment provided by INTELSAT, Inmarsat, or any successor entity or separated entity."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idce03d9cc-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/624/tVI/s643"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–624, title VI, § 643","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/180/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–180, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-03-17"},"text":"Mar. 17, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/56"},"text":"114 Stat. 56","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idce03d9cd-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idce03d9ce-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idce03d9cf-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Communications Act of 1934, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652"},"text":"act June 19, 1934, ch. 652","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/1064"},"text":"48 Stat. 1064","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 5 (§ 151 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t47/s609"},"text":"section 609 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
